The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for power system security assessment, which involves handling large amounts of data and making predictions based on that data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on the use of deep neural networks for image processing and prediction. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve topics such as control systems, optimization, and software engineering, which are important for power system security assessment.
